Description of incident: "On October 28, 2016, BraceAbility, Inc. learned of a possible security incident involving its online ordering website. We immediately engaged independent IT forensic experts to assist with our investigation. While the investigation is  still  ongoing,  it  appears  that  your  credit  or  debit  card  data  may  have  been  compromised  if  you  made  an  online  purchase between September 24, 2016 and November 28, 2016. The information potentially exposed includes your name, address, card number, verification code, and/or the card’s expiration date as well as information related to your online purchase."More information: https://oag.ca.gov/ecrime/databreach/reports/sb24-65407
